Descriptor.0: EMFISIS>Electric and Magnetic Field Instrument Suite and Integrated Science

TEXT.0: Wave Normal Analysis products, based on L1 spectral matrix survey E and B data, and produced via PRASSADCO (Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). A correction for antenna sheath effects has been applied to the electric field data, before being input to PRASSADCO. The correction is density-dependent, so fill values are inserted for E-dependent data where a density estimate is not available.

TEXT.1: Be aware that the spin-plane E antennas began deployment at 2012-09-13T19:44, and were not fully deployed until 2012-09-22T19:48. The spin-axis deployment began on 2012-09-24T17:59 and did not fully complete until 2012-12-07T04:41. Noise levels in the E data are increased by incomplete antenna deployment.

TEXT.2: There was a significant upgrade to the onboard calibration tables, for both E and B in Feb 2013. Prior to this, the highest survey frequency bin (11.24 kHz) used a flawed cal value that resulted in both amplitude and phase errors. The effect is stronger for the B data. New, corrected, tables took effect at 2013-02-12T04:30:00.

TEXT.3: In Mar 2013, there was a ~2-day interval where a software issue resulted in the wrong calibration tables being used for both E and B data. These data should be used with extreme caution. The interval is 2013-03-21T06:53:00 to 2013-03-23T05:46:00.

Logical_source_description.0: Probes-A EMFISIS wave normal angle products and sheath corrected electric field level Level-4

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Epoch

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Epoch at midpoint of the 0.468 second sampling interval for survey data.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: WFR_frequencies

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Average frequency of the set of FFT frequencies that were combined when creating the frequency bins for the spectral matrix data.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Power Spectral Density of B!bparallel!n

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Sum of the Three Magnetic Power Spectral Densities
Sum of Two Perpendicular Magnetic Power Spectral Densities

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Perpendicular components are along axis1 (outward) and axis2 (eastward).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Coherence Between B!bperp1!n and B!bperp2!n

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Coherence Between B!bperp1!n and B!bpar!n

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Coherence Between B!bperp2!n and B!bpar!n

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Power Spectral Density of E!bparallel!n

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with Z along B0, X outward from the Earth, and Y eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Power Spectral Density of E!bparallel!n Using Faraday Law

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). Coordinate system is field-aligned, with Z along B0, X outward from the Earth, and Y eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Sum of the Three Electric Power Spectral Densities
Sum of Two Perpendicular Electric Power Spectral Densities

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Perpendicular components are along axis1 (outward) and along axis2 (eastward).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Sum of Two Perpendicular Electric Power Spectral Densities Using Faraday Law

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Perpendicular components are along axis1 (outward) and along axis2 (eastward).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Degree of Polarization of The Magnetic Field From Eigenvalues

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Eigenvalues are determined using the SVD method (Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Ellipticity of the Magnetic Field Polarization

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Determined using the SVD method, from eq. 13 of Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Degree of Magnetic Field Polarization in the Polarization Plane

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Determined using the SVD method, from eq. A6 in the appendix of Santolik, et al., J. Geophys. Res., 107(A12), 1444, 2002.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Planarity of the Magnetic Field Polarization

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Determined using the SVD method, from eq. 12 of Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Electromagnetic Planarity

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Electromagnetic planarity calculated from the 6x6 spectral matrix using eq. 24 of Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Polar Angle of the Wave Vector

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Wave Normal Angles are determined using the SVD method (Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). Angle is measured from axis3, but all angles are 0 <= theta <= 90, due to ambiguity in the SVN method. Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Azimuthal Angle of the Wave Vector

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Wave Normal Angles are determined using the SVD method (Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003). Angle is measured counterclockwise from axis1. Coordinate system is field-aligned, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Spectral Density of the Poynting Flux

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Polar Angle of the Poynting Vector

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Angle is measured from axis3. Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Azimuthal Angle of the Poynting Vector

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Angle is measured counterclockwise from axis1. Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Spectral Density of the Poynting Flux Using Faraday Law

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Polar Angle of the Poynting Vector Using Faraday Law

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Angle is measured from axis3. Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Azimuthal Angle of the Poynting Vector Using Faraday Law

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Angle is measured counterclockwise from axis1. Poynting flux is directly computed from the E and B spectral data, in the field-aligned system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward. Does not use measured spin-axis E data when calculating E components in field-aligned system. Spin-axis E is synthesized from the two spin-plane E and all three B components, using Faraday law and plane-wave assumption (Sec. 3.3, Santolik, et al., Radio Sci., 38(1), 1010, 2003).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Geocentric radial distance to spacecraft
Magnetic Latitude of spacecraft
Magnetic Local Time of spacecraft
L Shell of spacecraft
Transformation Matrix, Antenna-Frame->Field-Aligned Coordinates

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: If V is a vector field value in the antenna frame [u, v, w], then Tuvw2fac ## V is that same quantity in the field-aligned coordinate system, with axis3 along B0, axis1 outward from the Earth, and axis2 eastward

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Buvw, nT

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The 3-vector B field from the EMFISIS MAG instrument in the spacecraft antenna coordinate system, with axis3 (w) along the spin-axis, axis1 (u) and axis2 (v) in the spin plane. Value is a linear interpolation between the two nearest (in time) magnetometer measurements to the specific epochs in this CDF.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Flag Indicating Spacecraft in Eclipse

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of 1 for a record indicates that spacecraft was in eclipse at the epoch of that record.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Flag Indicating Thruster Firing

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of 1 for a record indicates that spacecraft thrusters were firing at the epoch of that record.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Flag Indicating Spacecraft Charging Event

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of 1 for a record indicates that there was a spacecraft charging event at the epoch of that record. A charging event is defined as when the average of either pair of spin-plane EFW probes ((V1+V2)/2 or (V3+V4)/2) is > 2 V. Use caution interpreting electric field data during such an event.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Flag Indicating Anti-sunward Ew Antenna is Shadowed

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of 1 for a record indicates that the anti-sunward E antenna (probe 5) was shadowed by some other part of the spacecraft within 0.4 second of the epoch of that record.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Interpolated density

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Density value used when calculating the sheath corrections to E data. Based on densities derived from the upper-hybrid resonance line, but interpolated to the specific epochs in this CDF. Will be Fill when no density value is available. See rbsp-a_density_emfisis-L4_*.cdf files for the source densities.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Magnitude of Sheath Correction for Eu

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Magnitude of the sheath correction applied to the Eu antenna spectral density data. Raw data are effectively multiplied by this number to produce corrected data (actual magnitude and phase corrections are applied in a single operation in the complex domain). Coordinate system is the spacecraft antenna system, with axis3 (w) along the spin-axis, axis1 (u) and axis2 (v) in the spin plane. Fill values indicate that no correction was applied.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Phase of Sheath Correction for Eu

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Complex phase of the sheath correction applied to the Eu antenna spectral density data. Raw data effectively have this number added to their complex phase to produce corrected data (actual magnitude and phase corrections are applied in a single operation in the complex domain). Coordinate system is the spacecraft antenna system, with axis3 (w) along the spin-axis, axis1 (u) and axis2 (v) in the spin plane. Fill values indicate that no correction was applied.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Magnitude of Sheath Correction for Ev

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Magnitude of the sheath correction applied to the Ev antenna spectral density data. Raw data are effectively multiplied by this number to produce corrected data (actual magnitude and phase corrections are applied in a single operation in the complex domain). Coordinate system is the spacecraft antenna system, with axis3 (w) along the spin-axis, axis1 (u) and axis2 (v) in the spin plane. Fill values indicate that no correction was applied.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Phase of Sheath Correction for Ev

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Complex phase of the sheath correction applied to the Ev antenna spectral density data. Raw data effectively have this number added to their complex phase to produce corrected data (actual magnitude and phase corrections are applied in a single operation in the complex domain). Coordinate system is the spacecraft antenna system, with axis3 (w) along the spin-axis, axis1 (u) and axis2 (v) in the spin plane. Fill values indicate that no correction was applied.

Raw data are effectively multiplied by this number to produce corrected data (actual magnitude and phase corrections are applied in a single operation in the complex domain).
